<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Endemic to Ecuador (Azuay, Zamora-Chinchipe [expected]). It grows in marshy places of the paramo ecoregion, between elevations of 3050-3070 m (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Distribution map of Xenophyllum acerosum (left hand) and X. humile (right hand)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.158.50848.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448886" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Thus far, 
<taxonomicName genus="X." lsidName="X. acerosum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="acerosum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. acerosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from the type locality in the paramo of Yacumbi, which is located above Saraguro on the border between the Ecuadorian provinces of Azuay and Zamora-Chinchipe.
</paragraph>
